# Frontend React Standards

## Structure
- Functional components only; extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- All API calls through `frontend/src/api/client.ts`
- Vite dev proxy: `/api` → `http://localhost:8000`

## Code Quality
- TypeScript strict mode; no `any` unless unavoidable with a comment
- Colocate component styles or use `index.css` utility classes consistently

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML: `main`, `nav`, `button`, `label`, `form`
- Every interactive element needs an accessible name (visible label or `aria-label`)
- Form fields must have associated `<label htmlFor="...">`
- Visible keyboard focus styles; no click-only `div` buttons

## Efficiency
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders; memoize expensive derived values
- Fetch only what the UI needs; handle loading and error states
